"...woah...freaky stripes."\par
Not one second awake, and her attention was grabbed.\par
Up. Back. Around. She was sure now. It was everywhere. \par
Okay, not everywhere. She stood in a clean circle, completely free of...it.\par
Everywhere else? It was there.\par
For her, at that moment, that's all there was. Just her...and a gigantic cloud of swirling shadows.\par
Either had to be a billion, or just one. Sorta hard to tell. \par
Just, dark streaks. They flew past each other, over each other, and into each other. Or was it out of each other? And yet, no wind, no sound. If she had her eyes shut...well, maybe she would still see it?\par
But, boy, was it intense to see. Looked like it wanted to tear itself apart. But at the same time, staying obediently behind the invisible line. Like a mosh pit in a public bus, rocking out behind the yellow line. \par
Trying to track all the different kinds of shadows made her eyes spin and her head confused.  \par
"Ugh, what I am even looking at?!" \par
Jade looked away, but then quickly turned back, tilting her head, "...but ya know, it kinda looks like that time the TV went funny for a week straight. After Uncle decided it was full of demons and tried to exorcise it." \par
She shook her head, horrible memories returning. \par
"One \b whole week\b0  of squinting through dark, fuzzy lines over everything. Last time I try to watch '\i Top 30 Demon Summoning Movie Scenes\i0 '." \par
The nega-tornado re-grabbed her attention. And she kept staring for a bit before snapping back to the present. \par
"Wait. Why I am I staring at shadow static anyway?! Urgh!! I need to get out of her!" \par
But just then, she caught something. Faint, but it was there. \par
She'd recently become sensitive to fine details. Maybe from all the staring past unwanted flickers to catch the flickers she wanted to see? \par
Sure made up for the days of weird shimmers over her eyes.\par
Tohru and her once went to some apartment that held a 'Mahjong Thursdays'. Trying to make out any one thing in the place was impossible. But, sometimes, through all the tile slapping, gossip sharing, cigarette smoke wafting, and wild gesturing, she'd catch the owner. \par
Tiny guy, real quiet, wore nothing but paisley. He would slip through the noise and Jade would catch a glance of him. Then, he'd vanish. Swallowed back into the crowded room.  \par
Same deal here. The shadows had layers. And peering through them, someone was behind it all. \par
Literally. \par
As always, she knew how she felt about the matter.\par
"Alright, I definitely gotta go in now, Chan-style, and see what's going on for myself!" \par
She quickly caught herself. \par
"Well, uh, not 'see'. Since its all, ya know, all dark...who am I talking to??"\par
WIth a deep breath and a confident step, she continued, "Whatever. I just gotta go in, and pull whatever's there out into the...uh...light?"\par
Looking around, something became clear. That even where she stood, there wasn't really any light. She couldn't see her own hair dangling past her nose. \par
Well, kinda couldn't? \par
She didn't get it but in this hyper dark, she could 'see' everything she needed to. No details lost, whatever counts as 'details' here. There might as well be light to her.\par
"But it's different. It's not like super bright, but I feel like I can see way more here than I ever can at Uncle's shop at night."\par
Being able to see in what she knew was total darkness was messing with her mind. That's something for later-Jade, now-Jade needed to do some shadowdiving. \par
Right up to the invisible line, where the swarm began. A cautious arm was raised.\par
"Hope they don't eat my hand," she muttered before plunging it into the mass. The rest of her quickly reeled back. She gritted her teeth, closed her eyes and felt...nothing. \par
"Phew, guess that's not surprising for a bunch of shadows." \par
Even relieved, the arm stayed up, and she began trekking through the sightless fog. \par
"I wonder if this is like that episode of '\i Calvador: Cave Explorer\i0 ', where he finds a tunnel that went straight into an old prison?" \par
\par
\f3\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\f2\par
\par
The swarm went on for ages. \par
She was getting annoyed. \par
Where did the shadows end? Was there even anything out here? \par
Before an answer could pop into her mind, something solid popped into existence in her outstetched palm, making her jump.\par
"Ahh!" \par
She tapped the sudden mass a couple of times.\par
"Huh? Clothing? Wait is this--?" \par
A back. It was someone's back. \par
Squinting through the blurry dim didn't reveal much, just a vague silhouette. \par
"Uhh, hey, buddy. Any chance you got a light on ya? Ooorrrr know the way out?"\par
They turned slowly. She looked up straight where the face would be. Glowing, red eyes, peered back at her. \par
"Wait..." \par
But it lasted only for an instant. They popped. Shadow tendrils burst out through their clothes, sending Jade running back. \par
Their essence spewed everywhere. \par
Or, maybe, started sucking everything in?  \par
Either way, her view disappered. It flowed and flowed, pulling all the little streaks into a dead void. \par
The darkness even poured over her, removing her sense of form and presence in this world.\par
And then, it was all still, and cold.\par
"Uh oh. Bad day."\par
The emptiness felt...well, she didn't know what it felt like. But it wasn't fun. \par
She wanted to go home, now.\par
"...\i m\i0 ..."\par
"Who's there??" \par
Jade spun at the soft noise. Nothing around her. Though, who knows what 'around' was anymore.\par
Once again, a sound softly scratched through, "...\i c\i0 ...\i th\i0 ..."\par
She felt like something terrible was about to happen, and all she could do was shut her eyes and clench her hands tight. She went still and focused her thoughts on anything that could get rid of this void.\par
"Uhh, sunlight, flashlights, fireworks...uh, uh, come on Jade, what else?" \par
She pulled herself in tighter and tighter, near ready to implode, before...\par
\par
\f3\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\u10022?\f2\par
\par
"Wahhh!" \par
Her eyes snapped open and her arms flew all about. She huffed frantically. \par
It was dream, or something like that. \par
She was barely covered with sheets but slathered in a slimy slick all over her skin. As she got up, she felt it trickle down her back whilst also sticking her shirt to her body. \par
"Ewwww."\par
Jade threw herself out of her hot bed damp with sweat. She hopped into her fuzzy slippers and hurried to the bathroom. A stepping stool was pulled out and she leapt up to go face-to-face with the sink mirror. Neither side blinked, and she went further in, leaning in as far as possible and checking her eyes. \par
Red, puffy, a little unfocused, but definitely clear.\par
She sighed, her head now relieved of worry falling into the sink.\par
"Nice. No freaky shadows." Her head jerked up again, "Wait. Why would I even be checking for that?! Urgh..." before sinking again, "...and why am I still so sick...?"\par
Her strained throat kicked out a couple of coughs that shook her whole body. Just holding onto the sink left her arms wobbling. Combining all that with the rushed dash she just did left her feeling like a drifting boat - a hot, slimy one - caught out in a tide. \par
Descending the stool, she let herself collapse and brace against the cool bathtub on the even cooler, tiled floor.\par
Her head buoyed uncomfortably for a bit, her thoughts scattered and numbed out. But one thought did jump out. \par
"What time is it...?"\par
A heavy push off the outer tub, followed by a bit of crawling, let her poke her head back into her room. \par
The wall clock showed all zeroes. \par
Not even close to breakfast. Great.\par
She retreated to the bathtub, finding an even colder spot.\par
"Haahhh. That was...quite the dream, if you can even call it that. Geez, give me something a bit less '\i Elm Street\i0 ', could ya buddy?" She said, grabbing her head, even shaking it a bit. \par
She quickly lost energy and just sat, motionless. \par
"...maybe it's just 'cuz I'm sick. Tohru did say that sickness can make your body do weird things."\par
With Jackie, Tohru and Uncle gone since yesterday, and her with a high fever, she was left all alone at Section 13. Well, not exactly 'all alone'. \par
They did assign her a 'caretaker', partly because she was sick. \par
But mostly because she's Jade.\par
It was going to be a long week till they returned, she realised.\par
"Ugh, it's too early for this. I'm heading to bed."\par
But she didn't move. She groaned, coughed, and sighed one more time, then closed her eyes.\par
\par
