Something...scratchy whistled in her ears. It was too low to make out but gave her the creeps with how it sounded. \par
Almost familiar.\par
The pain eventually subsided and she opened her eyes. \par
Lifting her head, she found herself surrounded by staff, with worried looks and questions like '\i Are you okay? \i0 ' and '\i Where are her parents?\i0  '. \par
