Making magic Jade-style didn't work this time. The mojo wasn't flowing and everything came out baaaaad. It was like everytime she tried making something, walls appeared in her head and she lost track of what she was doing. Reading wasn't easy either, not with her headache  deciding to interrupt her every thought.\par
Suddenly another pulse in her head caused Jade to jerk up in pain.\par
"Urgh! Again?!" \par
She jerked a bit too hard, and the chair slipped, sending her to the ground, hard. \par
"Hah, smooth move, Jade."\par
Trying to push herself back up only had the response her tired arms and pounding headache sending her back down. After trying three times, and falling ungracefully each time, she thrashed around furious.\par
"Why?! Why this stupid cold gotta happen to me now of all times?!"\par
She collapsed tired. "If I could just make \b\i one \b0\i0 good spell, or even do \b\i anything\b0\i0  without feeling like hacking up a kidney...then I'd...I'd..."\par
Another heavy sigh, and she threw her head back, closing her eyes and ready to wait until her body starting working again. But, just as she decided on this, that sound, that unnerving sound came back.\par
"\i Call...them...\i0 "\par
That was definitely someone. \par
Her eyes snapped open. Swiveling her head around didn't reveal anything in the dark store, so a tentative response was made, "Call, who?"\par
"\i Call...them...\i0 "\par
She shivered everytime she heard that voice, it made her feel something bad. Something like...Uncle's willies that he kept going on about.\par
But in this moment of weak exhaustion, calling for help seemed better than being stuck on the floor. \par
A deep sigh came out, "Okay. Whoever you are, help me up, okay?"\par
Hands grab her at that moment, pulling her onto her feet. \par
About to thank her helpers, she instead recoilled, "Shadowkhan?! What? Why? What's happening?! This is isn't real!" A large crowd of them surrounded her, all gathered in the tiny room. \par
"This, this is...this is..." \par
A sudden calm came over her as she recognised this feeling of deja vu. \par
"...this is just like the time I got that freaky tattoo and became..." \par
Gazing around the room full of demons put it all together, but the cursed voice spoke up instead.\par
"\i Queen of the Shadowkhan.\i0 "\par
This made Jade spin in place, looking for the voice.\par
"You definitely exist! Who are you! Show yourself!"\par
"\i Me...me...\i0 "\par
It was fading again. It was all fading. The voice and the ninjas. \par
"Wait, no! Tell me! What do you want!?"\par
